The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, August 29, 2002  Smart Ruler lifts Colts Stakes 
 BY STAR RACER				 										Calcutta: Quoted at crammed odds of 2-10 despite his heavyweight, Smart Ruler returned a handsome winner of the 1,400m Calcutta Colts Trial Stakes on Wednesday. Amyn Merchant, who partnered the well-bred Razeen-Regal Star son to victory, helped trainer Daniel David notch up four winners in afternoons seven-event race-card.				 										In a three-horse-contest and from the same stable, Smart Rulers superiority was never in doubt from the word go. Merchant had him nicely settled behind Moon Quest till the half-way stage and let loose the rein to cruise home for a shade over four-length victory over the 5-1 second-favourite Royal City. 				 										Merchant-David combination went on the claim the Wise Guy Cup when Immaculate thrashed his five rivals Midas Touch in Cap-A-Pie Handicap and Lively Project in the Tangaroa Handicap helped the duo complete their days tally.. H. S. Baths Rheinheart lifted the Stirabout Cup.
